\title{ 
Ridge and Jet Distributions at Low $p_t$
and Large $\eta$
}


\author{Cheuk-Yin Wong}
\date{\today}

\maketitle

In order to get some estimate of the forward rapidity ridge structure,
we need to rely on associated particles with low $p_t$ for which the
number of counts can be large enough for meaningful measurement.  The
counting rate for large $p_t$ and large rapidity is not high enough to
minimize statistical errors.

We therefore need a reasonable description of the associated particles
with low transverse momenta.


